Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addTSV(25.10)                                                    addTSV(25.10)

Name
       addTSV  -  Adds TSVs, front-side bumps, and backside bumps under speci-
       fied conditions

Syntax
       addTSV

       [-help]

       [-noRouteBlkg]

       {[-frontBump <bumpCellName>]  [-backBump  <bumpCellName>]  [-tsvViaName
       <viaName>]}

       [-frontBump   <bumpCellName>  [-loc_type  {geometry_center|cell_center}
       -prefix <prefixName>] [-stackViaUnderBump <stackViaName>]]

       [-backBump  <bumpCellName>   [-loc_type   {geometry_center|cell_center}
       -prefix <prefixName>]]

       [-tsvViaName <viaName> [-noPlaceBlkg  | -spacing s]

           [[[-tsvFeedthru  {x  y}  [-stackViaTopLayer <layer>]] | [-stripeNet
       <pgnetName>

           -stripeLayer <layerNum>]] | [-stackViaName <stackViaName>  [-stack-
       ViaMarkerLayer      <markerLayerName>][-stack_via_array      {x      y}
       -stack_via_pitch {x y}]]]]

       {-lowerLeftLoc {x y}}

        [-relative_bump_cell   <bumpCell>   |    -relative_selected_bump    ]}
       {[-pitchxy  {x  y}]  [-relative_bump_cell  <bumpCell>  |  -relative_se-
       lected_bump ]}

       {[-upperRightLoc {x y} | -numxy {x y}] [-relative_bump_cell  <bumpCell>
       | -relative_selected_bump ]}}

       [{-relative_bump_cell  <bumpCell>  |  -relative_selected_bump } [-rela-
       tive_min_pitch <float>] [-relative_offset {x  y}]  [-relative_bump_type
       {signal power ground}]]

       [-perim <n>]

       [-stagger]

       Adds  TSVs, front-side bumps, and backside bumps under specified condi-
       tions. Use this command to create TSVs  and  bumps  after  the  initial
       floorplan is loaded.

Parameters
       -tsvViaName <viaName>
              Specifies  the name for TSV via defined in the LEF file. If this
              option is not specified, no TSV will be created.

              The following arguments are used only with tsvViaName:

              * noPlaceBlkg

              * spacing

              * tsvFeedthru

              * stackViaTopLayer

              * stripeNet

              * stripeLayer

       -frontBump<bumpCellName>
              Specifies the name for the front-side bump cell. If this  option
              is not specified, no front-side bump will be created.

       -backBump <bumpCellName>
              Specifies the name for the backside bump cell. If this option is
              not specified, no backside bump will be created.

       -loc_type {geometry_center|cell_center}
              Specifies the location type for bump creation.

              * geometry_center:  Specifies to use bump pin geometry to create
                bump

              * cell_center: Specifies to use bump bounding box to create bump

              This option is used with the -frontBump and -backBump options.

       -lowerLeftLoc x y
              Specifies (in microns) the lower left coordinate of the  box  in
              which TSV/Bumps will be created.

       -numxy x y
              Specifies (in microns) the count of the TSV/bump in the horizon-
              tal and vertical direction.

       -perim <n>
              Creates  TSV,  front-side  bumps,  and  backside bumps along the
              rings on the perimeter.

              If -perim is specified, <n>defines the number of rings. Then you
              can create TSV in the following ways:

              * Define the lower left and upper right location of the ring  by
                -lowerLeftLoc  and -upperRightLoc, and then the pitch value of
                x and y direction by -pitchxy. For example, the following com-
                mand creates TSV in which the lower-left is at {x1 y1} and the
                upper-right is at {x2 y2}

                addTSV -lowerLeftLoc {x1 y1} -upperRightLoc {x2  y2}  -pitchxy
                {px py} -stagger -perim 1

                                 *********

                                 *       *

                                 *       *

                                 *       *

                                 *       *

                                 *********

              * Define  the  lower left location of the ring by -lowerLeftLoc,
                and then specify the number and pitch value of tsv in x and  y
                directions  by -numxy and -pitchxy, respectively. For example,
                the following command creates TSV in which the lower  left  is
                at {x1 y1}

                -lowerLeftLoc {x1 y1} -numxy {12 8} -pitchxy {px py} -perim 2

                                 ************

                                 ************

                                 **        **

                                 **        **

                                 **        **

                                 **        **

                                 ************

                                 ************

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Adds a prefix name for a bump during bump creation and bump map-
              ping. The prefix name is not added to the TSV.

       -relative_bump_cell <bumpCell>
              Creates  TSV or bumps by default at the geometry center of bumps
              with specified bump cell.

       -relative_bump_type {signal power ground}
              Creates the relative bump type, TSV, or bumps by default at  the
              geometry center of bumps with the specified bump type.

       -relative_min_pitch <minPitch>
              Specifies  the minimum pitch between the created bumps/TSVs. The
              pitch between all the created bumps/TSV should  be  larger  than
              specified  min pitch. The -relative_min_pitch option is optional
              and  can  be  used  only  if   -relative_bump_cell/-relative_se-
              lected_bump is specified.

       -relative_offset {x y}
              Specifies  the offset of created bump/TSV location compared with
              the relative bump. The geometry center of the  created  bump/TSV
              is the geometry center of the relative bumps plus the offset.

              -relative_offset  is  optional  and  can  be used only if -rela-
              tive_bump_cell/-relative_selected_bump is specified.

       -relative_selected_bump
              Creates TSV or bumps by default at the geometry  center  of  the
              selected bumps.

       -upperRightLoc x y
              Specifies  (in microns) the upper right coordinate of the box in
              which TSV/Bumps will be created.

       -pitchxy <x y>
              Specifies (in microns) the distance between TSV centers in the x
              and y direction.

       -stagger
              Staggers (offsets) the TSV/bump array. For example:

              without -stagger       with -stagger

               * * * * *             * * * * *

               * * * * *              * * * *

               * * * * *             * * * * *

               * * * * *              * * * *

              * * * * *            * * * * *

       -noPlaceBlkg
              The placement blockage overlapped with TSV cut will be added  as
              default if -noPlaceBlkg is not specified.

       -noRouteBlkg
              The  routing  blockage  for each crossing layer will be added if
              -noRouteBlkg is not specified.

       -tsvFeedthru <sizex sizey>
              Creates the feedthru. sizeX and sizeY are the dimensions, in mi-
              crons, for the stack vias aligned with the TSV.

              Note: Feedtrhu is a collection of components including TSV,  the
              stacked via (from the first metal to the top metal) aligned with
              the TSV, and two bumps on the frontside and backside.

       -stackViaMarkerLayer <markerLayerName>
              Specifies the mark layer name.

              Mark cut layer of stack via as specified mark layer.

       -stackViaName <stackViaName>
              Specifies the stack via cell name.

              The  tool  automatically adds the specified via cell stacking to
              the top layer of long TSV.

       -stackViaTopLayer <layer>
              Defines the top layer that the TSV structure should connect  to.
              For  example, if you specify M5 for this parameter, Innovus will
              create a structure like TSV+VIA12+M2+VIA23+M3+.....+M5. This pa-
              rameter must be used with  -tsvFeedthru.

       -stackViaUnderBump <stackViaName>
              Specifies the stack via name under the front bump.

              The tool automatically adds the specified via cell  stacking  to
              the bottom layer of front-side bump.

       -stripeNet <pgnetName>
              Declares  that the TSV will be added beneath the power stripe, a
              stack via will be generated to touch the power stripe,  and  the
              new added TSV will be assigned by the power or ground net of the
              power stripe.

              Note:  This  options  should be used along with the -stripeLayer
              option.

       -stack_via_array {x y}
              Specifies the number of columns and rows for the stack  via  ar-
              ray.

              The  -stack_via_array  and  -stack_via_pitch options can only be
              specified when  -stackViaName is specified. -stack_via_array and
              -stack_via_pitch are specified at the same time.  The  value  of
              -stack_via_pitch  should  be  larger than stack via size. Other-
              wise, the stack via will overlap each other and cause DRC.

       -stack_via_pitch {x y}
              Specifies the pitch_x and pitch_y of the stack via.

              The -stack_via_array and -stack_via_pitch options  can  only  be
              specified when  -stackViaName is specified. -stack_via_array and
              -stack_via_pitch  are  specified  at the same time. The value of
              -stack_via_pitch should be larger than stack  via  size.  Other-
              wise, the stack via will overlap each other and cause DRC.

       -stripeLayer <layerNum>
              Specifies the layer number or layer name for the stripe net when
              adding TSV under stripe net.

              Note: This option should be used along with -stripeNet option.

       -spacing s
              Specifies  the  placement blockage size. Blockage size = TSV cut
              size + 2*s. If this option is not specified, "s"  will  be  with
              the value defined in LAYER TSV session in LEF file.

        At least one option of the following arguments is required for the ad-
       dTSV command:

              * tsvViaName

              * frontBump

              * backBump

Examples
              * The following command creates a 10 x 10 TSV array with a pitch
                of 40 microns and the lower left at (300 300):

                addTSV -lowerLeftLoc 300 300 -numxy 10 10 -pitchxy 40 40 -tsv-
                ViaName TSVVIA

              * The following command creates a backside array in box (300 300
                700 700) with a pitch of 40 microns:

                addTSV  -lowerLeftLoc  300 300 -upperRightLoc 700 700 -pitchxy
                40 40 -backBump BUMPCELL

Related Information
              * assignTSV

              * deleteTSV

